  "prompt": "Is there any app like Shazam to get the chord tabs when hearing a song?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several apps that can help you identify chords and provide tabs for songs as you listen to them. Here are a few popular options:\n\n1. **Chordify**: This app allows you to upload or link to a song, and it will generate the chord progression for you. It is particularly useful for guitarists and other instrumentalists looking for chord tabs.\n\n2. **Ultimate Guitar**: While primarily a site for chord and tab arrangements, the Ultimate Guitar app has a feature that allows users to search for tabs by entering the song title. They also have a \"Tabs\" section where users can find popular songs and their respective chord charts.\n\n3. **Yousician**: This app provides lessons for various instruments and includes a feature that helps you learn songs by listening to them. While it might not generate chords in real-time like Shazam, it gives you the option to learn how to play songs with chord diagrams.\n\n4. **AudioStretch**: Although it's more of a practice tool, this app allows you to slow down music and figure out chords and tabs by ear. It\u2019s useful for musicians trying to learn songs on their own without provided tabs.\n\n5. **Songsterr**: This app combines a tab player with a vast repository of tabs for various songs, and while it doesn't identify chords in real-time, you can search for nearly any song to find accompaniment.\n\n6. **Riffstation**: This app was designed to help users figure out chords from songs, but it has been discontinued. However, similar features may exist in other music education apps.\n\nThese tools can assist you in learning and playing your favorite songs by ear. Always be sure to check the app store for the latest music identification and chord-finding applications, as new options frequently emerge.",
